File: The case against controversial leader of the Enlightened Christian Gathering Church, Shepherd Bushiri and his wife Mary has been postponed to 29 November. PRETORIA - The case against controversial leader of the Enlightened Christian Gathering Church Shepherd Bushiri and his wife Mary has been postponed to 29 November. The couple appeared briefly at the Specialised Commercial Crimes Court in Pretoria on Thursday morning. WATCH: Hands off our prophet say Bushiri congregants Crowds gathered outside the court in support of the pair. The two were arrested in February and face fraud and money laundering charges. WATCH: Bushiri has no access to private jet They also face charges for contravening the Prevention of Organised Crime Act. The couple was granted R100,000 bail in February.